@node ARMYA "Army Ants"

@{b}Army Ants@{ub}

Color   = Black/Red
Rarity  = VI(U)
Type    = Summon Insects (1/1)
Cost    = 1BR
Artist  = G. Darrow & I. Rabarot

Text(VI): <T>, Sacrifice a land: Destroy target land.

Flavor Text: @{i}``Do not underestimate the power of many against one.''
             -Sidar Jabari@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node BREAT "Breathstealer's Crypt"

@{b}Breathstealer's Crypt@{ub}

Color   = Blue/Black
Rarity  = VI(R)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 2UB
Artist  = Blackie del Rio 

Text(VI): Whenever any player draws a card, he or she reveals that card.
          If the card is a creature card, that player pays 3 life or
          discards the card.

Flavor Text: @{i}``Far too many soldiers have died in their beds.''
             -Telim'Tor@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_B.guide/BREAT}

@endnode
@node CORRO "Corrosion"

@{b}Corrosion@{ub}

Color   = Black/Red
Rarity  = VI(R)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 1BR
Artist  = Michael Danza 

Text(VI): Cumulative upkeep: <1>
          During your upkeep, put a rust counter on each artifact target
          opponent controls. If the number of rust counters on an artifact
          equals or exceeds that artifact's casting cost, bury the artifact.
          If Corrosion leaves play, remove all rust counters from the game.

Flavor Text: @{i}No Flavor Text

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_C.guide/CORRO}

@endnode
@node FEMER "Femeref Enchantress"

@{b}Femeref Enchantress@{ub}

Color   = Green/White
Rarity  = VI(R)
Type    = Summon Enchantress (1/2)
Cost    = GW
Artist  = D. Alexander Gregory
 
Text(VI): Whenever an enchantment is put into any graveyard from
          play, draw a card.

Flavor Text: @{i}``Then she spread a fine dust over the land, like
             a butterfly shaking its wing.''
             -``The Enchantress,'' Femeref tale

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_F.guide/FEMEN}

@endnode
@node FIRES "Firestorm Hellkite"

@{b}Firestorm Hellkite@{ub}

Color   = Blue/Red
Rarity  = VI(R)
Type    = Summon Dragon (6/6)
Cost    = 4UR
Artist  = Pete Venters

Text(VI): Cumulative upkeep: <UR>
          Flying, Trample

Flavor Text: @{i}``If it can scar the sky with fire, do not share its
             destination.'' -Mwani, Mtenda herder

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node GUIDI "Guiding Spirit"

@{b}Guiding Spirit@{ub}

Color   = White/Blue
Rarity  = VI(R)
Type    = Summon Angel (1/2)
Cost    = 1WU
Artist  = Terese Nielsen

Text(VI): Flying
          <T>: If the top card of target player's graveyard is a creature
          card, put that card on the top of that player's library.

Flavor Text: @{i}``Retainer of eternal Sun! Life flash again upon thy wings.''
             -``Song to the Sun,'' Femeref song

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node MUNDU "Mundungu"

@{b}Mundungu@{ub}

Color   = Blue/Black
Rarity  = VI(U)
Type    = Summon Wizard (1/1)
Cost    = 1UB
Artist  = Terese Nielsen

Text(VI): <T>: Counter target spell unless that spell's caster pays an
          additional <1> and 1 life. Play this ability as an interrupt.

Flavor Text: @{i}``Our buried kings silently await the revolt of dead
             peasants.'' -Tuwile, mundungu of Aku

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node PYGMY "Pygmy Hippo"

@{b}Pygmy Hippo@{ub}

Color   = Green/Blue
Rarity  = VI(R)
Type    = Summon Hippopotamus (2/2)
Cost    = GU
Artist  = Steve White

Text(VI): If Pygmy Hippo attacks and is not blocked, you may choose to have
          it deal no combat damage this turn. If you do, defending player
          draws all mana from his or her lands and then his or her mana pool
          is emptied. After combat, add an equal amount of colorless mana to
          your mana pool.

Flavor Text: @{i}No Flavor Text

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_P.guide/PYGMY}

@endnode
@node RIGHT "Righteous War"

@{b}Righteous War@{ub}

Color   = White/Blue
Rarity  = VI(R)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 1WB
Artist  = Ian Miller

Text(VI): All white creatures you control gain protection from black.
          All black creatures gain protection from white.

Flavor Text: @{i}``This is a war without neutrality.''
             -Asmira, Holy Avenger

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
